<div class="row background-green">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 padding white">
        <div class="tree-display balsam" id="tree-display">
          <div class="tree-icons">
            <i class="fa fa-tree fa-3x" id="tree-icon">Balsam Fir</i>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h4>Name: Abies balsamea</h4>
        <h4>Heights: <%= Tree.all.includes(:type).select { |tree| tree.type.name == 'Balsam Fir' }.map(&:height).sort.join(', ') %>ft.</h4>
        <h4>Description:</h4>
        <p>Balsam fir is a beautiful pyramidal tree with short, flat, long-lasting, aromatic needles. Balsam fir and Fraser fir have many similar characteristics and some botanists consider them extensions of the same species. Balsam fir has a nice, dark green color and is very fragrant.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 padding white">
        <div class="tree-display fraser" id="tree-display">
          <div class="tree-icons">
            <i class="fa fa-tree fa-3x" id="tree-icon">Fraser Fir</i>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h4>Name: Abies fraseri</h4>
        <h4>Heights: <%= Tree.all.includes(:type).select { |tree| tree.type.name == 'Fraser Fir' }.map(&:height).sort.join(', ') %>ft.</h4>
        <h4>Description:</h4>
        <p>The Fraser fir is quickly becoming the most premium species of the cut Christmas tree market. Its mild fragrance, shape, strong limbs, and ability to retain its soft needles for a long time when cut make it one of the best trees for this purpose. It is characterized by a heavy density and is known for its deep hues of blueish green.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
